34static void
35x86_cpu_intel(wordptr cpu, yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86, unsigned int data)
36{
37 BitVector_Empty(cpu);
38
39 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_Priv);
40 if (data >= PROC_286)
41 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_Prot);
42 if (data >= PROC_386)
43 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SMM);
44 if (data >= PROC_skylake) {
45 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SHA);
46 }
47 if (data >= PROC_broadwell) {
48 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_RDSEED);
49 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_ADX);
50 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_PRFCHW);
51 }
52 if (data >= PROC_haswell) {
53 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_FMA);
54 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_AVX2);
55 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_BMI1);
56 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_BMI2);
57 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_INVPCID);
58 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_LZCNT);
59 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_TSX);
60 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SMAP);
61 }
62 if (data >= PROC_ivybridge) {
63 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_F16C);
64 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_FSGSBASE);
65 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_RDRAND);
66 }
67 if (data >= PROC_sandybridge) {
68 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_AVX);
69 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_XSAVEOPT);
70 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_EPTVPID);
71 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SMX);
72 }
73 if (data >= PROC_westmere) {
74 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_AES);
75 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_CLMUL);
76 }
77 if (data >= PROC_nehalem) {
78 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE42);
79 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_XSAVE);
80 }
81 if (data >= PROC_penryn)
82 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE41);
83 if (data >= PROC_conroe)
84 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSSE3);
85 if (data >= PROC_prescott)
86 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE3);
87 if (data >= PROC_p4)
88 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE2);
89 if (data >= PROC_p3)
90 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE);
91 if (data >= PROC_p2)
92 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_MMX);
93 if (data >= PROC_486)
94 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_FPU);
95 if (data >= PROC_prescott)
96 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_EM64T);
97
98 if (data >= PROC_p4)
99 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_P4);
100 if (data >= PROC_p3)
101 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_P3);
102 if (data >= PROC_686)
103 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_686);
104 if (data >= PROC_586)
105 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_586);
106 if (data >= PROC_486)
107 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_486);
108 if (data >= PROC_386)
109 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_386);
110 if (data >= PROC_286)
111 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_286);
112 if (data >= PROC_186)
113 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_186);
114 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_086);
115
116 /* Use Intel long NOPs if 686 or better */
117 if (data >= PROC_686)
118 arch_x86->nop = X86_NOP_INTEL;
119 else
120 arch_x86->nop = X86_NOP_BASIC;
121}

123static void
124x86_cpu_ia64(wordptr cpu, yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86, unsigned int data)

153static void
154x86_cpu_amd(wordptr cpu, yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86, unsigned int data)
155{
156 BitVector_Empty(cpu);
157
158 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_Priv);
159 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_Prot);
160 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SMM);
161 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_3DNow);
162 if (data >= PROC_bulldozer) {
163 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_XOP);
164 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_FMA4);
165 }
166 if (data >= PROC_k10)
167 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE4a);
168 if (data >= PROC_venice)
169 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE3);
170 if (data >= PROC_hammer)
171 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE2);
172 if (data >= PROC_k7)
173 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE);
174 if (data >= PROC_k6)
175 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_MMX);
176 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_FPU);
177
178 if (data >= PROC_hammer)
179 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_Hammer);
180 if (data >= PROC_k7)
181 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_Athlon);
182 if (data >= PROC_k6)
183 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_K6);
184 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_686);
185 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_586);
186 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_486);
187 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_386);
188 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_286);
189 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_186);
190 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_086);
191
192 /* Use AMD long NOPs if k6 or better */
193 if (data >= PROC_k6)
194 arch_x86->nop = X86_NOP_AMD;
195 else
196 arch_x86->nop = X86_NOP_BASIC;
197}

209}

211static void
212x86_cpu_set_sse4(wordptr cpu, yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86, unsigned int data)
213{
214 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE41);
215 BitVector_Bit_On(cpu, CPU_SSE42);
216}

219x86_cpu_clear_sse4(wordptr cpu, yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86, unsigned int data)

222 BitVector_Bit_Off(cpu, CPU_SSE42);
223}

622
623void
624yasm_x86__parse_cpu(yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86, const char *cpuid,
625 size_t cpuid_len)
626{
627 /*@null@*/ const struct cpu_parse_data *pdata;
628 wordptr new_cpu;
629 size_t i;
630 static char lcaseid[16];
631
632 if (cpuid_len > 15)
633 return;
634 for (i=0; i<cpuid_len; i++)
635 lcaseid[i] = tolower(cpuid[i]);
636 lcaseid[cpuid_len] = '\0';
637
638 pdata = cpu_find(lcaseid, cpuid_len);
639 if (!pdata) {
640 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
641 N_("unrecognized CPU identifier `%s'"), cpuid);
642 return;
643 }
644
645 new_cpu = BitVector_Clone(arch_x86->cpu_enables[arch_x86->active_cpu]);
646 pdata->handler(new_cpu, arch_x86, pdata->data);
647
648 /* try to find an existing match in the CPU table first */
649 for (i=0; i<arch_x86->cpu_enables_size; i++) {
650 if (BitVector_equal(arch_x86->cpu_enables[i], new_cpu)) {
651 arch_x86->active_cpu = i;
652 BitVector_Destroy(new_cpu);
653 return;
654 }
655 }
656
657 /* not found, need to add a new entry */
658 arch_x86->active_cpu = arch_x86->cpu_enables_size++;
659 arch_x86->cpu_enables =
660 yasm_xrealloc(arch_x86->cpu_enables,
661 arch_x86->cpu_enables_size*sizeof(wordptr));
662 arch_x86->cpu_enables[arch_x86->active_cpu] = new_cpu;
663}
